      "text": [
        "اَ «نَعَمْ إِنَّ اَلدَّارَ وَ اَلْخَادِمَ لَيْسَا بِمَالٍ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1627 - Abu Ja'far (Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir) and Abu Abdullah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) were asked about a man who owns a house, a servant, and a slave. \"Can he accept Zakat?\"\nThey (as) replied: \"Yes, because the house and the servant are not considered wealth.\""
        ]
      }
